info: This type of thing makes me want to have a Lucene component or something else more IR-based. Networks isn't an area. It might or might not appear in the title of a course; it's more likely to appear in the description, but SQL isn't super-awesome at partial matches. Also, this is going to give us every class that mentions "network"; IR has spent a long time figuring out better approaches.
paraphrases: Among the Computer Science classes offered , is there a class about networks ?
Are there any classes about networks ?
Do they offer a class about networks ?
Does a class about networks exist ?
I would be interested in a class about networks . Does that exist ?
Is networks a class that is offered ?
Is there a class that focuses on networks ?
Of the classes , is there 1 about networks ?
Regarding networks , Is there a class ?
To learn about networks , is there a class offered here ?
What classes about networks are there ?
With regards to classes , are there any about networks ?
sentence: Is there a class about networks ?
sentence-with-vars: Is there a class about networks ?
sql: SELECT COURSEalias0.DEPARTMENT , COURSEalias0.DESCRIPTION , COURSEalias0.NAME , COURSEalias0.NUMBER FROM COURSE AS COURSEalias0 WHERE ( DESCRIPTION LIKE "%network%" OR NAME LIKE "%network%" ) AND COURSEalias0.DEPARTMENT = "EECS" ;
